docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:10:The user asked for source grounding in high-energy physics, especially around theories of time and matter. The cards added here are intended to keep future Lumenary research disciplined when it makes bridges between contemplative philosophy, time, matter, fields, symmetry, and cosmology.
docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:18:- Time in relativity and field theory: Einstein, Minkowski, Noether, and direct time-reversal violation in B mesons.
docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:19:- Quantum-gravity time: problem of time, partial observables, Page-Wootters stationary dynamics, and the Wheeler-DeWitt lineage.
docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:26:3. Use `Noether Invariant Variation Problems`, `Einstein On The Electrodynamics Of Moving Bodies`, and `Minkowski Space And Time` to distinguish temporal experience from coordinate time and symmetry structure.
docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:27:4. Use `BABAR Observation Of Time Reversal Violation` only for physical T-violation, not broad claims about psychological time or spiritual transformation.
docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:28:5. Use `Anderson The Problem Of Time In Quantum Gravity`, `Rovelli Partial Observables`, `Page And Wootters Evolution Without Evolution`, and `DeWitt Quantum Theory Of Gravity The Canonical Theory` for emergent/relational time hypotheses.
docs/high-energy-physics-source-grounding-2026-05-25.md:41:The preferred intellectual move is not "physics proves mysticism." It is: physics supplies hard constraints on time and matter concepts, and those constraints can expose where spiritual language is precise, overextended, or unexpectedly structurally similar.
